<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="690" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[797,1386,877,1305]" lastBlockId="63.[180,1389,1311,3471]" pageId="63" pageNumber="690">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[801,922,960,989]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="690" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephus">C. cephus</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1216,1337,960,989]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="690" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephus">C. cephus</taxonomicName>
superspecies group as defined byJ. Kingdon in his 1997 Field Guide to African Mammals. It also includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1774" box="[1048,1218,1083,1108]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="690" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petaurista">C. petaurista</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1904" box="[1246,1378,1083,1108]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="689" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sclateri">C. sclateri</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1838" box="[801,961,1122,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="688" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythrotis">C. erythrotis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Audebert" authorityYear="1799" box="[989,1146,1122,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="687" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ascanius">C. ascanius</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1866" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="689" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erythrogaster">C. erythrogaster</taxonomicName>
. C. P. Groves in his 2001 Primate Taxonomy had the same composition for his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[800,882,1236,1265]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="690" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephus">cephus</taxonomicName>
species group. Albinism has been reported. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1187,1269,1272,1305]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Cercopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="63" pageNumber="690" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cephus">cephus</taxonomicName>
hybridizes with C. e. camerunensis in a small area just to the south of the Sanaga River nearits mouth, between Tinaso and Lake Tisongo. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
